content: Lots of customization options and interactivity.   Just started using it.   Not sure on battery life yet but so far so good.  Give it a shot.

Serious Battery Killer. This watch face is very cool.  I love the layout and the configurable widgets, but there are multiple issues with the app/face that make it a not-recommended in my book. The first and most obvious is that it is a serious battery killer.  Running this watch face drained my battery from 100% to 38% in less than five hours.  When I deleted the face from my phone the watch lasted another 6 hours on that remaining 38%.  No other change in usage, so it was clearly this app. Another issue is the steps counter was wrong.  It was over-reporting the steps by 30% compared to what other step counters reported at the same time. Finally, the watch face is not AMOLED friendly.  There is no true black background to pick, which means you can't save battery life by keeping a lot of the AMOLED pixels off. I'd request a refund if I could.  This app a good example of why you should get 24 hours to refund an app!
replyContent: Hi, Concerning the battery, this should not happen. Please try to uninstall and reinstall the watch face, and take a look if it gets better. It should be stable once you have done using the different settings to get your favorite preset. Concerning amoled, you have an option to put the hands in Strings mode. Most pixels will be off. Keep me inform
